comments: Powell (DAL) jumps vertically and absorbs the contact that occurs during Beal's (WAS) layup attempt.
Powell (DAL) is already in Kuzma's (WAS) path and absorbs the contact during the screen.
Doncic (DAL) legally contests Beal's (WAS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Powell (DAL) makes marginal contact to Avdija's (WAS) back while rebounding.
Dinwiddie's (DAL) leg dislodges the ball out of the bounds. WAS retains the possession.
Beal (WAS) engages with Green (DAL) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Beal releases away to retrieve the pass.
Green (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position and incidental contact occurs as he defends Beal (WAS) during the drive.
Beal (WAS) goes to, not through, Green (DAL) and incidental contact occurs as they come together at the end of the drive.
Green (DAL) establishes himself in Avdija's (WAS) path before Avdija has started his upward motion, and since Avdija slips most of the contact, a no call would have been the best outcome.
Kuzma (WAS) is moving alongside Doncic's (DAL) path and marginal body contact occurs at the end of Doncic's drive.
Doncic (DAL) makes marginal contact to Kuzma's (WAS) front as he releases away on his stepback jump shot.
Doncic (DAL) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Beal (WAS) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Avdija (WAS) makes contact to Doncic's (DAL) arm which affects his driving shot attempt.

Doncic (DAL) moves laterally into Kuzma's (WAS) path and initiates body contact that affects Kuzma's SQBR during the drive.  Replay review of the foul called on Doncic (DAL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful.
Wright (WAS) extends his leg out and makes intentional foot to ball contact.
Wright's (WAS) leg dislodges the ball out of bounds. Mavericks retains the possession.
Wright (WAS) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Doncic (DAL) as he attempt to make a pass.
